com.whitespike.visionstructure

Class Env

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.whitespike.visionstructure.Env

  • public class Env
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the top level structure of the api, a digital representation of an environment generated by the raw data received.
    Author:
    Jonah Schreiner

    • Constructor Detail

      • Env

        public Env(boolean includeHigherSenses,
           boolean includeImaginarySenses)
        Constructor which allows the user to determine which types of senses are found.
        Parameters:
        includeHigherSenses - Should the api find higher senses (relate senses to those that contain them. Ex: a rectangle and a handle are combined to create a door sense).
        includeImaginarySenses - Should the api find imaginary senses (Ex: Rows, Columns, Arrays of senses/objects).

      • Env

        public Env(int xOffset,
           int yOffset,
           int width,
           int height)
        Env constructor used for only working on a subsection of the display (usually used for testing/demos).
        Parameters:
        xOffset - X pos of the top left coordinate of the subimage (top left of image is 0,0)
        yOffset - Y pos of the top left coordinate of the subimage (top left of image is 0,0)
        width - Width of the subimage.
        height - Height of the subimage.

      • Env

        public Env(int xOffset,
           int yOffset,
           int width,
           int height,
           boolean includeHigherSenses,
           boolean includeImaginarySenses)
        Env constructor used for only working on a subsection of the display (usually used for testing/demos). Includes the higherSense and imaginarySense finding parameters.
        Parameters:
        xOffset - X pos of the top left coordinate of the subimage (top left of image is 0,0)
        yOffset - Y pos of the top left coordinate of the subimage (top left of image is 0,0)
        width - Width of the subimage.
        height - Height of the subimage.
        includeHigherSenses - Should the api find higher senses?
        includeImaginarySenses - Should the api find imaginary senses?
